<div class="question-card" id="card-110" data-qid="110" data-type="single">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 111</span>
    <span class="q-tag single">Single Choice</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      Refer to the exhibit. What is wrong with the displayed termination?
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-110">
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">The untwisted length of each wire is too long.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">The woven copper braid should not have been removed.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">The wrong type of connector is being used.</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">The wires are too thick for the connector that is used.</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn" id="submit-110" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-110">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-110"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        When a cable to an RJ-45 connector is terminated, it is important to ensure that the untwisted wires are not too long and that the flexible plastic sheath surrounding the wires is crimped down and not the bare wires. None of the colored wires should be visible from the bottom of the jack.
      </div>
    </div>
